def: A green micaceous mineral occurring in minute scales. It isessentially a silicate of aluminia and potash containing vanadium.
To free from possession by a devil or evil spirit; to exorcise.[Obs.]They boy having gotten a habit of counterfeiting . . . would not beundeviled by all their exorcisms. Fuller.
Gradually decreasing; past the acme, or crisis, as a distemper.Dunglison.

Capable of neutralizing four molecules of a monacid base;having four hydrogen atoms capable of replacement by bases;quadribasic; -- said of certain acids; thus, normal silicic acid,Si(OH)4, is a tetrabasic acid.
Irreverent. [Obs.]Immodest speech, or irreverend gesture. Strype.

The state, quality, or relation of being objective; characterof the object or of the objective.The calm, the cheerfulness, the disinterested objectivity havedisappeared [in the life of the Greeks]. M. Arnold.
A member or inhabitant of a colony.
By right; of right; by law; -- often opposed to be facto.
